The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the label lengths. Additionally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms for distance labeling, which is related to algorithms and complexity (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.SI).
